ing onto Arusha.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels at Lush Garden Hotel or similar . Room upgrade available on this day.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Morning Game Drive in the Ngorongoro Crater</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>6</day1><day2>6</day2><destfrom>Fly to Zanzibar &amp; Stone Town</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today we are bound for the enigmatic, intoxicating Isles of Zanzibar. We will transfer to Arusha Airport to take our flight to the paradise island. Arriving in Zanzibar we head to Stone Town where we will spend our first night on the Island.</p><p>On arrival at our hotel in Stone Town you are free to explore the labyrinth of walled streets, winding alleys, bustling markets and grand crumbling architecture. This UNESCO-listed Stone Town has changed little over the past 200 years. If you enjoy shopping then there are plenty of crafts and colourful souvenirs to be purchased here. Admire the intriguingly decorated doors before sitting down to watch the sun set with a fresh juice, cold beer or cocktail. If the thought of fresh seafood gets the taste buds tingling, make sure you check out the excellent night market on the promenade which serves a feast not to be missed!</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels at Safari Lodge or similar . Room upgrade available on this day.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>7</day1><day2>7</day2><destfrom>Zanzibar North Beach &amp; Spice Tour</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today we head to Nungwi Beach. On the way we will stop at one of the many spice plantations where we can discover the abundant plants that flourish in this verdant, tropical environment and sample spices picked straight from the source. We will also visit a small village, having the chance to interact with the locals and experience their kind hospitality; here we will enjoy a traditional lunch cooked by the community.</p><p>We will arrive in Nungwi early afternoon and start enjoying this sun kissed paradise. Indulge in a cocktail or two while we watch the sunset over the crystal clear Indian Ocean.</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels at Nungwi Inn or similar . Room upgrade available on this day.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals><includedexcursions>Zanzibar spice tour &amp; local lunch,Traditional Local Lunch</includedexcursions></itinerary><itinerary><day1>8</day1><day2>8</day2><destfrom>Zanzibar North Beach</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Today you are free to relax on the white coral sands or enjoy one of the many water based activities on the island. Snorkel with colourful marine life or simply kick back and soak up the sun. This beautiful setting will certainly provide you with a chance to relax and unwind!</p></description><accommodation>1 night(s) in hotels at Nungwi Inn or similar . Room upgrade available on this day.</accommodation><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary><itinerary><day1>9</day1><day2>9</day2><destfrom>Depart Zanzibar North Beach</destfrom><destto></destto><description><p>Your adventure of a lifetime comes to an end today.  If you have a late flight or have lengthened your stay by adding post tour accommodation you will have more time to explore the sights.</p> <p>Your adventure of a lifetime comes to an end today.  If you have a late flight or have lengthened your stay by adding post tour accommodation you will have more time to explore the sights.</p></description><meals>1 Breakfast(s)</meals></itinerary></itineraries><availabilities><availability><departdate>2021-01-25</departdate><quantity>7+</quantity><guaranteed>false</guaranteed><specialnotes></specialnotes><prices><price><currency>AUD</currency><value>2910.04</value><rack>3829.00</rack><discount>-918.96</discount><Description>Discount </Description></price><price><currency>CAD</currency><value>2689.64</value><rack>3539.00</rack><discount>-849.36</dis